    • Method Detail

      • attachKeyStrokeListener

        public static void attachKeyStrokeListener​(@NonNull
                                           java.lang.String category,
                                           @NonNull
                                           java.lang.String className,
                                           @NonNull
                                           java.lang.String elementName,
                                           @NonNull
                                           android.widget.EditText field)
        Listen for keystrokes on a edit text field.
        Parameters:
        category - the category associated with the edit text field where the list of valid categories is defined in MetricsUtils.
        className - provide the classname for the recording. Do not use getClass().getName() as this will generally be obfuscated on release builds.
        elementName - the element name to identify the specific edit text
        field - the field to be monitored - please note that this will override the View.OnKeyListener, EditText.OnEditorActionListener and View.OnFocusChangeListener. If you want to record the actions of a edittext, please see recordKeyStroke

      • record

        public static void record​(@NonNull
                          java.lang.String category,
                          @NonNull
                          java.lang.String event,
                          @NonNull
                          java.lang.String className,
                          @NonNull
                          java.lang.String elementName,
                          @NonNull
                          android.os.Bundle details)
        Record information relevant to a specific android widget
        Parameters:
        category - the category associated with this android widget metric record.
        event - one of the events for the provided category
        className - provide the classname for the recording. Do not use getClass().getName() as this will generally be obfuscated on release builds.
        elementName - the element name / widget name to identify the specific ui element
        details - the bundle of information to be recorded

      • record

        public static void record​(@NonNull
                          java.lang.String category,
                          @NonNull
                          java.lang.String event,
                          @NonNull
                          java.lang.String className,
                          @NonNull
                          java.lang.String info)
        Record information relevant to a specific android widget, This performs the same action as passing in a bundle with a DETAIL_FIELD_INFO instead of the info string parameter.
        Parameters:
        category - the category associated with this android widget metric record.
        event - one of the events for the provided category
        className - provide the classname for the recording. Do not use getClass().getName() as this will generally be obfuscated on release builds.
        info - the simple string information associated with the event

      • record

        public static void record​(@NonNull
                          java.lang.String category,
                          @NonNull
                          java.lang.String event,
                          @NonNull
                          java.lang.String className,
                          @NonNull
                          MapItem mapItem,

                          java.lang.String info)
        This performs the same action as passing in a bundle with a DETAIL_FIELD_INFO instead of the info string parameter.
